  .project-description
    .container-p
      %p.project-description
        The Doers engaged with Benetton's communication research centre, in order to drive Fabrica and Fabricanti - under the lead of capitain Dan Hill - through a process of organizational and cultural change that will reform and upgrade the way current, future and past Fabrica fellows interface with the digital domain of experiences.
      %p.project-description
        Process has started from the collaborative mapping of the Fabricanti’s (staff + alumni) and public user experience, “as is” and “to be”. Particular attention has been be paid to the: (1) process of alumni engagement, care and tracking, from first submission to the post-Fabrica experience;  (2) digital behaviour of Fabricanti’s, projects’ lifecycle, and distributed content production about projects, both as Fabrica’s alumni and professionals.
      %p.project-description
        Technololy & architecture is thought to: (1) be modular, (2) enable flexible integration of third party tools and services (also when third services allow to provide required features and can save development effort), (3) support user engagement through real time feedbacks and updates, (4) be as flat as possible (in terms of hierarchy), (5) foster fast browsing, search and aggregation of data/info (e.g. through filters and a non relational DB ), (6) support an image centred language (fast loading, optimization, proper caching...), (7) be easy to manage and useful to learn for Fabricanti.
      %p.project-description
        Mostly user generated, contents should prioritize storytelling about projects and people around them.
      %p.project-description
        Minimalist and finest, the graphic language is defined by Fabrica’s fellows, and executed by them under the direction of The Doers, in order to produce a web/ixd compliant proposal and a set of graphic objects suitable to be translated and optimized in the front end development of a responsive interface.
      %p.project-description
        Interaction design strategy is intended to promote users’ interaction with the digital hub, in a way that the emerging digital lifestyle is consistent with  (and/or could somehow address) the Fabrica’s culture (e.g.: no moderation but shared rules , open, democratic, trasparent, ...)
      %p.project-description
        Priorities respond to the following keywords: resilience, enhacement of Fabricanti’s (staff + alumni) experience, emergence of projects storytelling, user engagement, user generated content and social convergence.
